a:T72a,✨ The Soul of Himalayas – Infinite Yatra Signature Expedition

Kedarnath • Tungnath • Badrinath • 5 Prayag • Rishikesh • River Rafting

Step into a journey where every mountain breathes stories, every river carries ancient wisdom, and every moment reconnects you with your own soul.
This is not just a tour — this is a pilgrimage into the heart of the Himalayas.

🌄 Kedarnath — Where Faith Touches the Sky
Walk the sacred path to the divine Jyotirlinga, surrounded by towering peaks and the energy of centuries-old devotion.

🕉 Tungnath — The Highest Shiva Temple in the World
A trek that purifies the mind. A view that transforms the heart.
Here, the Himalayas whisper your purpose.

🌺 Badrinath — The Gateway to Moksha
Seek blessings at the holy shrine of Badri Vishal as the Alaknanda flows beside you like a guide from another lifetime.

🌊 Panch Prayag — The Confluence of Destiny
Witness the meeting of five sacred rivers:
Devprayag, Rudraprayag, Karnaprayag, Nandprayag, Vishnuprayag.
Each confluence is a spiritual milestone, a reminder that all paths eventually unite.

🌱 Rishikesh — Yoga Capital of the World
Experience the calm of Ganga Aarti, the purity of the ghats, and the vibrance of a town where seekers from every corner come to find peace.

⚡ River Rafting — Feel the Power of Ganga
Ride the waves of adventure as the Ganga flows wild and free — a thrilling reminder that life is meant to be lived boldly.

💫 Why We Call This Journey “The Soul of Himalayas”
Because this route isn’t just scenic — it is sacred.
It carries the essence of Shiva, the peace of the sages, the raw beauty of untouched mountains, and the energy that transforms a person from within.

When you return, you don’t just bring back photos — you bring back a new version of yourself.2:[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"TravelAgency\",\"name\":\"Infinite Yatra\",\"url\":\"https://infiniteyatra.com\",\"logo\":\"https://infiniteyatra.com/logo.png\",\"description\":\"Premium Indian tour packages for families, honeymoon couples, and adventure seekers. Destinations include Goa, Kashmir, Manali, Kerala and 50+ locations across India.\",\"telephone\":\"+919265799325\",\"email\":\"infiniteyatra@gmail.com\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressCountry\":\"IN\"},\"sameAs\":[\"https://instagram.com/infinite.yatra\",\"https://x.com/infiniteyatra\",\"https://www.whatsapp.com/channel/0029VbBX7rv3gvWStqSdXf08\"],\"currenciesAccepted\":\"INR\",\"openingHours\":\"Mo-Su 09:00-21:00\"}"}}],["$","$L9",null,{"featuredTours":[{"highlights":["Visit Gangotri & Yamunotri","Darshan at Kedarnath & Badrinath","Scenic Himalayan drive","Spiritual Ganga Aarti","Comfortable accommodation"],"discount":"","validDateRange":{"start":"2026-05-01","end":"2026-10-30"},"difficulty":"Moderate","faqs":[],"location":"Uttarakhand, India","bestTime":"May to October","priceDisplay":"₹35,000","displayOrder":999,"duration":"10 Days / 9 Nights","price":35000,"description":"Embark on the holy Chardham Yatra in 2026. Visit Gangotri, Yamunotri, Kedarnath, and Badrinath. Book now to avail early bird discounts!","goodToKnow":[],"whoIsThisFor":[],"itinerary":[{"day":1,"description":"Drive to Barkot via Mussoorie. Visit Kempty Falls.","title":"Haridwar to Barkot","activities":["Scenic drive","Waterfall visit"]},{"day":2,"title":"Barkot to Yamunotri","activities":["Trek","Temple darshan"],"description":"Trek to Yamunotri temple and return to Barkot."},{"description":"Drive to Uttarkashi. Visit Kashi Vishwanath Temple.","title":"Barkot to Uttarkashi","activities":["Temple visit","River view"],"day":3},{"description":"Drive to Gangotri, darshan, and return to Uttarkashi.","title":"Uttarkashi to Gangotri","activities":["Temple darshan","Ganga puja"],"day":4},{"day":5,"description":"Long drive to Guptkashi via Tehri Dam.","title":"Uttarkashi to Guptkashi","activities":["Scenic drive","Dam view"]},{"title":"Guptkashi to Kedarnath","activities":["Trek","Aarti"],"description":"Trek to Kedarnath. Evening Aarti.","day":6},{"title":"Kedarnath to Guptkashi","activities":["Darshan","Trek down"],"description":"Morning darshan and trek down.","day":7},{"day":8,"activities":["Scenic drive","Temple darshan"],"title":"Guptkashi to Badrinath","description":"Drive to Badrinath via Chopta."},{"title":"Badrinath to Rudraprayag","activities":["Darshan","Confluence view"],"description":"Morning darshan and drive to Rudraprayag.","day":9},{"description":"Drive back to Haridwar. Trip concludes.","title":"Rudraprayag to Haridwar","activities":["Return journey"],"day":10}],"maxAltitude":"11,755 ft","rating":5,"featuredOnHomepage":false,"isVisible":true,"tokenPrice":0,"title":"Chardham Yatra 2026","thingsToCarry":[],"exclusions":["Lunch","Personal expenses","Helicopter tickets"],"type":"custom","category":["spiritual","trek","backpacking"],"pickupDrop":"Haridwar & Rishikesh","images":["https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769243371/kwmghyumwadfbytwdkq1.webp","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769243442/om50lnbsoifbsdd06i1a.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769243445/a8we4cjuwgaoim91nhnk.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769243452/zvpo6c0kcok5qambau8e.png","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769243457/rxbt90wla6h7tjorvtcv.webp"],"inclusions":["Accommodation","Meals (Breakfast & Dinner)","Transportation","Guide"],"id":"chardham-2026","image":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769243348/zrkccxqmgjqdzftl76ee.png","maxGroupSize":16,"cancellationPolicy":["Token Amount: ₹1,000 per person (Non-Refundable & Non-Transferable)","More than 7 days before trip: Full refund minus token amount","4–7 days before trip: 50% refund only","Less than 72 hours / No Show: No refund"],"costPrice":25000},{"inclusions":["Dehradun to Dehradun Transport","Meals during trek","Camping equipment","Permits","Trek Leader"],"images":["https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769241930/cxypm59oy94whrcsrhew.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769241934/a9qnddzteyr8elwlrkwa.webp","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769241940/myfq8xt4klo8vlpsdvhc.webp","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769241944/ottxyq9tnxi1kadjgr0u.webp","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769423190/tgtrwggh0dlzrwsnu8gy.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769423196/dd71taxy8x1z2klef4eo.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769423200/n9ktx2rsouhgwryrqhoo.jpg"],"costPrice":4000,"id":"dayara-bugyal","image":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769242341/gidbciy6flfk4freo64w.jpg","maxGroupSize":15,"cancellationPolicy":["Token Amount: ₹1,000 per person (Non-Refundable & Non-Transferable)","More than 7 days before trip: Full refund minus token amount","4–7 days before trip: 50% refund only","Less than 72 hours / No Show: No refund"],"thingsToCarry":["👕 Clothing 2–3 quick-dry t-shirts 2 trekking pants Fleece jacket & padded/down jacket Thermal innerwear (top & bottom) Woolen socks, cap & gloves Raincoat or poncho 👟 Footwear Sturdy trekking shoes with ankle support Lightweight slippers/sandals 🎒 Trek Essentials Sunglasses with UV protection Torch/headlamp with extra batteries Trekking pole 2L water bottle or hydration pack Lip balm, sunscreen & moisturizer 🧴 Personal Care Wet wipes, hand sanitizer & toiletries Toilet paper & sanitary items 💊 Medical & Snacks Personal medicines & basic first-aid kit Energy bars, chocolates & dry fruits Government-issued ID proof (mandatory)"],"featuredOnHomepage":true,"isVisible":false,"title":"Dayara Bugyal Trek","packingList":[{"category":"Clothing","icon":"👕","items":["2–3 quick-dry t-shirts","2 trekking pants","Fleece jacket & padded/down jacket","Thermal innerwear (top & bottom)","Woolen socks, cap & gloves","Raincoat or poncho"]},{"items":["Sturdy trekking shoes with ankle support","Lightweight slippers/sandals"],"category":"Footwear","icon":"👟"},{"items":["Sunglasses with UV protection","Torch/headlamp with extra batteries","Trekking pole","2L water bottle or hydration pack","Lip balm, sunscreen & moisturizer"],"icon":"🎒","category":"Trek Essentials"},{"icon":"🧴","category":"Personal Care","items":["Wet wipes, hand sanitizer & toiletries","Toilet paper & sanitary items"]},{"items":["Personal medicines & basic first-aid kit","Energy bars, chocolates & dry fruits","Government-issued ID proof (mandatory)"],"category":"Medical & Snacks","icon":"💊"}],"tokenPrice":999,"pickupDrop":"Dehradun","exclusions":["Personal expenses","Rucksack offloading","Insurance"],"type":"custom","category":["trek"],"goodToKnow":["Mobile network limited after Raithal","ATM available only in Dehradun/Uttarkashi","Weather changes quickly"],"priceDisplay":"₹5,999","displayOrder":2,"duration":"4 Days / 3 Nights","description":"Dayara Bugyal is one of the most beautiful high-altitude meadows in the Himalayas, offering wide open grasslands, snow-covered trails, and breathtaking mountain views. This trek is perfect for beginners as well as nature lovers who want a peaceful yet adventurous Himalayan experience.\n\nThe journey takes you through dense forests, traditional villages, and vast alpine meadows with panoramic views of peaks like Bandarpoonch and Draupadi Ka Danda. Whether covered in snow during winter or lush green in summer, Dayara Bugyal feels magical in every season.\n\nWith Infinite Yatra, this trek is designed to be safe, well-guided, and memorable — balancing adventure, comfort, and natural beauty.\n\nExplore Infinite. 🏔️","price":5999,"rating":4.8,"whoIsThisFor":["Beginners","First-time trekkers","Fitness level: basic"],"itinerary":[{"stats":{"altitude":"7,070 ft","time":"7–8 hours","distance":"180 km"},"stay":"Homestay / Guesthouse","day":1,"title":"Dehradun to Raithal","activities":["Scenic mountain drive","Base camp arrival","Village stay"],"meals":"Dinner included","description":"Scenic drive from Dehradun to Raithal village via Uttarkashi. Raithal serves as the base camp of the trek, surrounded by oak forests and mountain views."},{"stats":{"time":"2–3 hours","altitude":"~9,800 ft","distance":"5 km"},"stay":"Camping at Gui","day":2,"description":"Begin the trek from Raithal to Gui campsite through dense oak and rhododendron forests. A gradual ascent ideal for acclimatization.","title":"Raithal to Gui Campsite","meals":"Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner","activities":["Forest trails","First campsite","Acclimatization walk"]},{"activities":["Dayara Bugyal meadows","Himalayan peaks views","Photography & snow (winter)"],"meals":"Breakfast, Packed Lunch & Dinner","title":"Gui to Dayara Bugyal & Back","description":"Summit day trek to the vast alpine meadows of Dayara Bugyal. Enjoy panoramic Himalayan views before returning to Gui campsite.","day":3,"stats":{"distance":"~4.3 km","time":"~3 hours","altitude":"~12,100 ft"},"stay":"Camping at Gui"},{"stats":{"driveDistance":"~180 km","distance":"~4 km (descent)","time":"7–8 hours total"},"title":"Raithal to Dehradun","meals":"Breakfast included","activities":["Easy downhill trek","Scenic return drive","Trek completion"],"description":"Descend from Gui to Raithal and drive back to Dehradun via Uttarkashi, marking the end of the trek.","day":4}],"maxAltitude":"11,181 ft","highlights":["Lush Green Meadows","Panoramic Mountain Views","Easy Trek for Beginners","Camping under Stars","Dehradun to Dehradun Transport"],"discount":"","faqs":[],"location":"Uttarakhand, India","bestTime":"Year Round","difficulty":"Easy to Moderate"},{"costPrice":45000,"cancellationPolicy":["Cancellations made 15+ days before departure: 90% refund","7-14 days before departure: 50% refund","Less than 7 days: No refund"],"maxGroupSize":25,"image":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769242423/thi1ordyjcsn0nlwy0bz.jpg","id":"dazzling-dubai","inclusions":["4 Nights Hotel Stay","Daily Breakfast","Airport Transfers","Desert Safari","Dhow Cruise","Burj Khalifa Tickets"],"images":["https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769243601/dvdjpykpudfym1x8yrae.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769243606/a6p2djjbzevykxqqo4rr.webp","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769243617/scuyhup9rvhwo8ymydgb.jpg"],"pickupDrop":"Dubai Airport","category":["international","honeymoon","leisure"],"type":"mixed","exclusions":["Flights","Visa Fees","Tourism Dirham Fee","Personal Expenses"],"thingsToCarry":[],"tokenPrice":4999,"title":"Dazzling Dubai","featuredOnHomepage":true,"isVisible":true,"rating":4.8,"itinerary":[{"day":1,"description":"Arrival at Dubai International Airport. Transfer to hotel. Evening Dhow Cruise with dinner.","activities":["Arrival","Dhow Cruise"],"title":"Arrival in Dubai"},{"title":"Dubai City Tour & Burj Khalifa","activities":["City Tour","Burj Khalifa"],"description":"Half-day city tour covering Jumeirah Beach, Atlantis, and Gold Souk. Evening visit to Burj Khalifa 124th floor.","day":2},{"description":"Morning at leisure. Afternoon pick up for Desert Safari with dune bashing, camel riding, and BBQ dinner.","activities":["Desert Safari","BBQ Dinner"],"title":"Desert Safari","day":3},{"day":4,"description":"Optional full-day tour to Abu Dhabi visiting Sheikh Zayed Mosque and Ferrari World, or spend the day shopping.","activities":["Abu Dhabi (Optional)","Shopping"],"title":"Abu Dhabi Tour / Leisure"},{"title":"Departure","activities":["Departure"],"description":"Check out and transfer to airport for your flight back home.","day":5}],"whoIsThisFor":[],"goodToKnow":[],"description":"Experience the glitz and glamour of Dubai. From the tallest building in the world to the vast desert dunes, this trip offers a blend of modern luxury and traditional Arabian culture.","price":59999,"duration":"5 Days / 4 Nights","priceDisplay":"₹59,999","displayOrder":4,"bestTime":"October to April","location":"Dubai, UAE","faqs":[],"difficulty":"Easy","discount":"","highlights":["Burj Khalifa - At the Top","Desert Safari with BBQ Dinner","Marina Dhow Cruise","Dubai Mall & Fountain Show","Abu Dhabi City Tour (Optional)"]},{"exclusions":["Personal expenses and tips","Insurance of any kind","Cost of any additional activities","Anything not mentioned in inclusions","Personal trekking gear (shoes, backpack, etc.)"],"category":["trek"],"type":"custom","pickupDrop":"Dehradun","isVisible":true,"featuredOnHomepage":true,"title":"Kedarkantha Trek","packingList":[{"items":["2–3 quick-dry t-shirts","2 trekking pants","Fleece jacket & padded/down jacket","Thermal innerwear (top & bottom)","Woolen socks, cap & gloves","Raincoat or poncho"],"icon":"👕","category":"Clothing"},{"items":["Sturdy trekking shoes with ankle support","Lightweight slippers/sandals"],"category":"Footwear","icon":"👟"},{"items":["Sunglasses with UV protection","Torch/headlamp with extra batteries","Trekking pole","2L water bottle or hydration pack","Lip balm, sunscreen & moisturizer"],"icon":"🎒","category":"Trek Essentials"},{"icon":"🧴","category":"Personal Care","items":["Wet wipes, hand sanitizer & toiletries","Toilet paper & sanitary items"]},{"category":"Medical & Snacks","icon":"💊","items":["Personal medicines & basic first-aid kit","Energy bars, chocolates & dry fruits","Government-issued ID proof (mandatory)"]}],"tokenPrice":999,"thingsToCarry":[],"id":"kedarkantha","cancellationPolicy":["Token Amount: ₹1,000 per person (Non-Refundable & Non-Transferable)","More than 7 days before trip: Full refund minus token amount","4–7 days before trip: 50% refund only","Less than 72 hours / No Show: No refund"],"image":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769244317/vfvpo4oaambfnk3yglio.png","maxGroupSize":12,"costPrice":3500,"gallery":[{"alt":"Stunning sunrise view from Kedarkantha summit with golden snow-covered peaks","url":"/images/gallery/kedarkantha-1.png","id":1},{"id":2,"url":"/images/gallery/kedarkantha-2.png","alt":"Trekkers hiking on snowy trail with Himalayan mountains in background"},{"alt":"Camping under starry night sky at Kedarkantha base camp","url":"/images/gallery/kedarkantha-3.png","id":3},{"alt":"Panoramic 360-degree view from Kedarkantha peak with prayer flags","url":"/images/gallery/kedarkantha-4.png","id":4},{"id":5,"alt":"Beautiful pine forest trail with snow and wooden bridge","url":"/images/gallery/kedarkantha-5.png"},{"id":6,"alt":"Traditional Uttarakhand village with Himalayan peaks in background","url":"/images/gallery/kedarkantha-6.png"}],"images":["https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1626621341517-bbf3d9990a23?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506905925346-21bda4d32df4?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1464822759023-fed622ff2c3b?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop"],"inclusions":["Accommodation in tents and guesthouse","All meals during the trek (breakfast, lunch, dinner)","Experienced trek leader and support staff","First aid medical kits and oxygen cylinder","Trekking equipment (tents, sleeping bags, etc.)","Forest permits and camping charges","Transportation from Dehradun to Dehradun"],"difficulty":"Moderate","faqs":[{"question":"What is the best time to do the Kedarkantha trek?","id":1,"answer":"The best time for Kedarkantha trek is from December to April, during the winter months. This is when you can experience snow-covered trails and stunning winter landscapes. December to February offers heavy snowfall, while March-April has moderate snow with clearer skies."},{"question":"Is Kedarkantha trek suitable for beginners?","id":2,"answer":"Yes, Kedarkantha is considered one of the best treks for beginners. The trail is well-marked, the altitude gain is gradual, and the trek duration is manageable. However, basic fitness and some prior walking/hiking experience is recommended."},{"id":3,"question":"What should I pack for the Kedarkantha trek?","answer":"Essential items include: warm layers (thermal wear, fleece jacket, down jacket), waterproof trekking shoes, gloves, woolen socks, sunglasses, sunscreen, water bottle, headlamp, and personal medications. We provide tents, sleeping bags, and technical equipment."},{"id":4,"question":"How difficult is the Kedarkantha trek?","answer":"Kedarkantha is rated as moderate difficulty. The trek involves 4-6 hours of walking daily with a maximum altitude of 12,500 ft. The trails are well-defined, but you'll encounter snow and steep sections near the summit. Good physical fitness is recommended."},{"answer":"We recommend this trek for people aged 10-65 years. Children should be accompanied by adults, and elderly trekkers should have a medical fitness certificate. Anyone with heart conditions, respiratory issues, or other serious health concerns should consult a doctor before booking.","question":"Are there any age restrictions for this trek?","id":5},{"answer":"Accommodation includes a mix of guesthouses in Sankri village and camping in alpine tents during the trek. All camping equipment including sleeping bags, mattresses, and dining tents are provided. Toilets are available at all campsites.","question":"What is the accommodation like during the trek?","id":6},{"answer":"Mobile network (BSNL and Jio) is available in Sankri village. However, connectivity becomes limited or unavailable once you start trekking. We recommend informing family members beforehand and carrying a power bank.","id":7,"question":"Is mobile network available during the trek?"},{"id":8,"question":"What about food during the trek?","answer":"We provide nutritious vegetarian meals including breakfast, lunch, and dinner. The menu includes parathas, rice, dal, vegetables, soup, tea, and snacks. We ensure hygienic food preparation and cater to dietary requirements if informed in advance."}],"bestTime":"December to April","location":"Uttarakhand, India","highlights":["Summit climb to 12,500 ft","Panoramic views of Himalayan peaks","Walk through pristine pine forests","Experience camping in snow","Visit ancient temples"],"discount":"","whoIsThisFor":[],"maxAltitude":"12,500 ft","itinerary":[{"description":"Drive from Dehradun to Sankri village (220 km, 8-10 hours). Enjoy scenic views of the Himalayas and Tons river. Overnight stay in Sankri.","activities":["Scenic drive","Village exploration","Acclimatization"],"image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506905925346-21bda4d32df4?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop","title":"Dehradun to Sankri","day":1},{"day":2,"image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1464822759023-fed622ff2c3b?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop","activities":["Forest trek","Lake visit","Camping"],"title":"Sankri to Juda Ka Talab","description":"Trek from Sankri to Juda Ka Talab (4 km, 4-5 hours). Walk through dense pine forests and reach the beautiful frozen lake. Camp overnight."},{"activities":["Mountain trek","Photography","Base camp setup"],"image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1519904981063-b0cf448d479e?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop","title":"Juda Ka Talab to Kedarkantha Base","description":"Trek to Kedarkantha base camp (4 km, 3-4 hours). Gradual ascent through oak forests with stunning mountain views. Overnight camping.","day":3},{"day":4,"title":"Summit Day - Kedarkantha Peak - Sankri","image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1626621341517-bbf3d9990a23?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop","activities":["Summit climb","Sunrise viewing","Descent to Sankri"],"description":"Early morning summit push to Kedarkantha peak (6 km, 6-7 hours round trip). Witness spectacular sunrise and 360-degree views. Descend to Sankri camp."},{"description":"Drive back to Dehradun (220 km, 8-10 hours). Trip concludes with beautiful memories of the Himalayas.","image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506905925346-21bda4d32df4?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop","activities":["Return journey","Trip conclusion"],"title":"Sankri to Dehradun","day":5}],"rating":5,"displayOrder":1,"priceDisplay":"₹5,999","price":5999,"description":"Kedarkantha is one of the most popular winter treks in India, offering stunning views of the Himalayan peaks. This trek takes you through beautiful pine forests, frozen lakes, and snow-covered meadows, culminating in a breathtaking summit climb.","duration":"5 Days / 4 Nights","goodToKnow":[]},{"availableDates":["2026-05-15","2026-05-22","2026-05-29","2026-06-05"],"inclusions":["Transport","Meals","Stay","Guide"],"price":12000,"description":"A spiritual journey to one of the holiest shrines of Lord Shiva. The Kedarnath trek offers a blend of spirituality and adventure, taking you through picturesque landscapes to the ancient temple standing tall amidst the Himalayas.","images":["https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1548013146-72479768bada?q=80&w=2076&auto=format&fit=crop","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1626621341517-bbf3d9990a23?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506905925346-21bda4d32df4?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1464822759023-fed622ff2c3b?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1519904981063-b0cf448d479e?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop"],"duration":"5 Days / 4 Nights","priceDisplay":"₹12,000","rating":4.9,"maxAltitude":"11,755 ft","image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1548013146-72479768bada?q=80&w=2076&auto=format&fit=crop","maxGroupSize":15,"itinerary":[{"day":1,"description":"Drive from Haridwar to Guptkashi. Check-in at hotel. Relax and prepare for the trek.","title":"Haridwar to Guptkashi","activities":["Scenic Drive","Hotel Check-in"]},{"day":2,"title":"Guptkashi to Kedarnath","activities":["Trek start","Evening Aarti"],"description":"Drive to Sonprayag/Gaurikund and start the trek to Kedarnath. Reach by evening and attend Aarti."},{"description":"Morning Darshan at temple. Trek down to Gaurikund and drive back to Guptkashi.","title":"Kedarnath Darshan & Return","activities":["Temple Darshan","Trek down"],"day":3},{"description":"Drive back towards Rishikesh. Explore the Yoga Capital.","title":"Guptkashi to Rishikesh","activities":["Drive","Rishikesh exploration"],"day":4},{"description":"Departure from Rishikesh/Haridwar.","title":"Departure","activities":["Departure"],"day":5}],"id":"kedarnath","title":"Kedarnath Trek","highlights":["Darshan of Kedarnath Temple","Trek through scenic landscapes","Witness the majestic Himalayas","Experience the spiritual aura","Camping amidst nature"],"bestTime":"May to June, September to October","location":"Uttarakhand, India","difficulty":"Moderate to Difficult","type":"mixed","exclusions":["Personal Expenses","Pony/Palki charges"]},{"goodToKnow":[],"duration":"","price":21999,"description":"","priceDisplay":"₹21,999","displayOrder":999,"itinerary":[{"day":1,"title":"","activities":[],"description":""}],"whoIsThisFor":[],"discount":"","highlights":[],"location":"Rajsthan","bestTime":"","faqs":[],"difficulty":"Moderate","inclusions":[],"images":["https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769241639/azgksak3qo6guy7b1eeu.png","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769595262/e4f8n2uqsomlefk414bv.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769595268/amrouqjshoajce9ojzrj.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769595277/etijclwbxvy1dlgalj5r.jpg"],"image":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769595251/g3ma56bmzuowdjmx9y92.jpg","maxGroupSize":0,"id":"rajsthan","thingsToCarry":[],"title":"Rajsthan","isVisible":true,"featuredOnHomepage":false,"pickupDrop":"Delhi","category":"leisure","exclusions":[]},{"costPrice":12500,"pdf":"/itineraries/IY_The_Soul_Of_Himalayas.pdf","cancellationPolicy":["Token Amount: ₹1,000 per person (Non-Refundable & Non-Transferable)","More than 7 days before trip: Full refund minus token amount","4–7 days before trip: 50% refund only","Less than 72 hours / No Show: No refund"],"maxGroupSize":16,"image":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769244678/drixdwjvckiizvlymg0r.jpg","id":"soul-of-himalayas","inclusions":["Accommodation","Meals","Transport","River Rafting"],"images":["https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245493/idmlmdg5jb2axtpfov7j.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245566/op56wkreizkaqvrklusy.webp","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245592/ob6frywsoxrd2adcnpxu.webp","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245600/l60lbetdlc2tkcuwa7wy.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245630/zuvpizyxutctmrokksk5.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245868/vshnmxcdxdzuooj3ual9.png","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245877/eltswjgnoyr5at7qfhl5.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245885/q6wiyo4xuvdrmkpleryh.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245891/xztbvkwgbmjxgqnwifmx.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245900/w0of6yflz5lvnnsivlfq.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245906/hgxm7fzhukcay63tyeuq.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245917/tgn0ctlskmncr3g6bhei.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245939/avhcghb1gyjfsmt74x6n.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245947/aifnfitjfnpauz6pu8ev.jpg","https://res.cloudinary.com/dsi4mdylh/image/upload/v1769245954/loxnpvmree5gs0kgs7fk.jpg"],"pickupDrop":"Haridwar & Rishikesh","category":["spiritual","trek"],"type":"custom","exclusions":["Personal Expenses"],"thingsToCarry":["Medicines"],"tokenPrice":0,"packingList":[{"category":"Footwear","icon":"👟","items":["Non-skid deep-treaded hiking shoes – Quantity: 1","Lightweight slippers/sandals – Quantity: 1 pair"]},{"items":["Track pants","Full-sleeve T-shirts (1 for every 2 days of trekking)","Undergarments (1 per day of trekking)","Rainwear (jacket & pants), raincoat, umbrella","Sun-shielding hat – Quantity: 1"],"icon":"👕","category":"Clothing"},{"items":["Personal toiletry kit (small towel, toilet paper, paper soap/bar soap, toothbrush, toothpaste, cold cream, etc.)"],"icon":"🧴","category":"Toiletries"},{"icon":"🔋","category":"Electronics","items":["Power bank","Camera with extra batteries (optional)"]},{"category":"Others","icon":"🍫","items":["Dry fruits, nuts, chocolate bars","Carry sufficient personal medicines (if required)","Consult your doctor before joining the trek","Sunscreen lotion, lip balm","Newspaper and plastic bags"]}],"title":"The Soul of Himalayas","featuredOnHomepage":true,"isVisible":true,"rating":5,"maxAltitude":"12,500 ft","itinerary":[{"day":1,"description":"Arrival description.","title":"Arrival","activities":["Arrival"]}],"whoIsThisFor":["For they want to know uttrakhand"],"goodToKnow":["Some places mobile network issue"],"description":"$a","price":17999,"duration":"7 Days / 6 Nights","displayOrder":3,"priceDisplay":"₹17,999","bestTime":"Year Round","location":"Uttrakhand, India","faqs":[],"difficulty":"Moderate","validDateRange":{"end":"2026-10-30","start":"2026-05-01"},"discount":"","highlights":["Kedarnath - Divine Jyotirlinga","Tungnath - Highest Shiva Temple","Badrinath - Gateway to Moksha","Panch Prayag - 5 Sacred Confluences","Rishikesh - Yoga Capital","River Rafting in Ganga"]},{"goodToKnow":[],"displayOrder":999,"priceDisplay":"₹35,000","duration":"6 Days / 5 Nights","price":35000,"description":"The perfect mix of city life and beach vibes. Explore the bustling streets of Bangkok and relax on the pristine beaches of Phuket.","rating":4.6,"whoIsThisFor":[],"itinerary":[{"day":1,"activities":["Arrival","Beach"],"title":"Arrival in Phuket","description":"Transfer to hotel. Evening at leisure/Patong Beach."},{"activities":["Island Tour","Snorkeling"],"title":"Phi Phi Island Tour","description":"Full day tour to Phi Phi Islands by speedboat with lunch.","day":2},{"day":3,"description":"Half day city tour. Visit Big Buddha and Wat Chalong.","title":"Phuket City Tour","activities":["Sightseeing"]},{"description":"Flight to Bangkok. Check-in. Evening Chao Phraya Cruise (Optional).","title":"Phuket to Bangkok","activities":["Flight","Transfer"],"day":4},{"day":5,"title":"Bangkok City & Temple Tour","activities":["Temple Tour","Shopping"],"description":"Visit Golden Buddha and Marble Temple. Shopping at MBK/Pratunam."},{"day":6,"description":"Transfer to airport.","title":"Departure","activities":["Departure"]}],"highlights":["Phi Phi Island Tour","Bangkok Temple Tour","Phuket City Tour","Beach Relaxation","Shopping in Bangkok"],"discount":"","faqs":[],"location":"Phuket & Bangkok, Thailand","bestTime":"November to April","difficulty":"Easy","inclusions":["Hotels","Breakfast","Airport Transfers","Phi Phi Tour"],"images":["https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1552465011-b4e21bf6e79a?q=80&w=2039&auto=format&fit=crop"],"costPrice":30000,"id":"thailand-tropical","maxGroupSize":20,"image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1552465011-b4e21bf6e79a?q=80&w=2039&auto=format&fit=crop","cancellationPolicy":["Cancellations made 15+ days before departure: 90% refund","7-14 days before departure: 50% refund","Less than 7 days: No refund"],"thingsToCarry":[],"isVisible":false,"featuredOnHomepage":false,"tokenPrice":0,"title":"Tropical Thailand","pickupDrop":"Phuket Airport","exclusions":["Flights (International/Domestic)","Visa on Arrival","Lunch & Dinner"],"type":"mixed","category":["international","honeymoon","leisure"]}]}]]
